  <!-- ============================================================
       FOUNDATION — two things that make this work
       Subtle card. Simultaneous work + consensus infrastructure.
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="concept-foundation" aria-labelledby="foundationTitle">
    <div class="concept-foundation__inner">
      <div class="concept-foundation__card">
        <h2 id="foundationTitle" class="concept-foundation__title">Two things that make this work.</h2>
        <div class="concept-foundation__columns">
          <div>
            <h3 class="concept-foundation__col-title">Twenty-four agents working at once.</h3>
            <p class="concept-foundation__col-body">
              Humans work in sequence — one task at a time, one decision at a time.
              <strong>Agents don't.</strong> While one is migrating a database, another is
              drafting customer replies, a third is rebuilding your search index, a fourth
              is shipping your weekly report. That isn't faster software. It's a different
              geometry of capacity — and it's the biggest advantage of running this way.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="concept-foundation__col-title">A consensus network you couldn't build alone.</h3>
            <p class="concept-foundation__col-body">
              Every receipt your agents write is cryptographically signed and posted to an
              <strong>enterprise consensus network</strong> — the same kind of distributed
              infrastructure that financial institutions use to settle billion-dollar
              transactions. Nothing in your operating history can be quietly altered.
              Nothing gets lost. The record is yours, permanent, and verifiable by anyone
              you grant access to.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

